The area

Address
Neighborhood: El Born / La Ribera
The labyrinth that is El Born becomes most apparent the moment you turn down one of its side streets. But this is one of the few labyrinths you might actually enjoy losing your way in. After all, there are few places that live and breathe such exciting energy regardless of the time of day. This neighborhood seamlessly transcends the old and new parts of the city, reflected in its vast array of restaurants ranging from fancy Michelin-star establishments to trendy fusion restaurants. Here you'll find historical and cultural attractions such as the popular Picasso Museum and the Gothic cathedral La Santa Maria del Mar, where you just might be able to catch a traditional Catalan wedding.

Una noche buena con baile flamenco!
Aug 2022
I loved my night at Palau Delmases where I enjoyed an intimate flamenco show and a complementary glass of tinto de verano (Spain's summer go-to drink). Although the show was entirely in Spanish, it did not diminish this native English speaker's experience. The performers truly came alive during the show and I felt moved by the performance. I would recommend getting there early as they don't allow late guests in.
The venue is also absolutely stunning. Before and after the show, take some time to relish in the beauty of the historic palace and perhaps even exchange a few words with other guests. This venue is near the Arc de Triumph, Picasso Museum, and a few other notable landmarks. You won't regret adding this stop to your travel itinerary.
